        passage: "<p>A scholar of ancient philosophy argues that a certain Greek term for artistic representation meant a great deal more than the simple, mechanical \"copying\" of the world, and that rendering it in modern translations merely as \"imitation\" flattens what was in fact a rich and many-sided idea. A student writing about the scholar's argument is looking for a quotation from another expert on ancient thought that would lend that argument support.</p>",
