        passage: "<figure style='margin:0 0 14px'><figcaption style='font-weight:600;text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px'>Two Reef Sites' Fish Before and After Protection</figcaption><table style='border-collapse:collapse;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.3'><thead><tr><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Site</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Fish per hectare, 2010</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Fish per hectare, 2020</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Change</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>Reef North</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>1,400</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>2,300</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>+64%</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>Reef South</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>1,600</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>1,500</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-6%</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Marine biologists counted the fish living per hectare at two nearby reef sites, once in 2010 and again a decade later, in 2020. Fishing was banned at Reef North beginning in 2011 but was allowed to continue, as before, at Reef South. After comparing the two sets of counts, the biologists concluded that the ban had given the fish population at Reef North the chance to recover. That conclusion is best supported by the observation that, in the years after the ban took effect, Reef North ______</p>",
