        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>\"Foundry Town\" is a 1919 poem by the (invented) poet Cyril Wren. The poem describes a town built around a single great iron foundry that runs day and night, and throughout the poem the speaker presents that foundry not as a mere lifeless workplace of brick and iron but as a living creature in its own right, one that breathes, that never rests, and that seems almost to watch over the town. The speaker conveys this sense of the foundry as a living thing most directly when writing, ______</p>",
