        passage: "<p>A student writing about an eighteenth-century mapmaker asserts that he improved and corrected his charts not only by relying on surveys carried out by trained government officials but also, and heavily, by drawing on reports sent back to him by ordinary working sailors. To support this assertion, the student is searching for a quotation from a historian who has closely studied the mapmaker's surviving papers and correspondence.</p>",
