        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>A student writing about a colonial-era weaver asserts that she was a genuine innovator in the craft of dyeing, inventing several of her own techniques rather than simply passing along methods that had been handed down to her by earlier weavers. To support this assertion, the student is looking for a quotation from a textile historian who has studied the weaver's surviving cloth, tools, and written papers in detail.</p>",
