        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>A student writing about an early street photographer asserts that she did not simply capture her scenes of city life by chance, as they happened to unfold, but rather staged them deliberately, posing and arranging her subjects with care before releasing the shutter. To support this assertion, the student is looking for a quotation from a historian who has closely studied the photographer's own notebooks together with her surviving glass negatives.</p>",
