        domain: "Information & Ideas",
        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>A species of cuttlefish can throw rapidly changing patterns across the surface of its skin. Researchers studying the animal proposed that the males use these shifting patterns above all as a way of communicating with rival males during their contests over territory and mates, rather than simply as a means of camouflaging themselves, blending in against the sand and rock of the seabed on which they rest.</p>",
