        domain: "Information & Ideas",
        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>\"The Ferryman\" is a 1913 poem by the (invented) poet Gregory Sallis. The poem describes an old ferryman who has spent his whole life rowing travelers back and forth across a single river. So many times has he made the crossing, over so many years, that the speaker comes to present him as belonging less to the town on either bank than to the river itself, as though the water had claimed him for its own. The speaker conveys this most directly when writing, ______</p>",
