        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<figure style='margin:0 0 14px'><figcaption style='font-weight:600;text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px'>Caspian Sea Level Recorded at Baku</figcaption><table style='border-collapse:collapse;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.3'><thead><tr><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Year</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Level (m below sea)</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Change from prior row (m)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>1995</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-26.6</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>--</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>2005</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-27.2</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-0.6</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>2015</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-28.0</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-0.8</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>2022</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-28.8</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>-0.8</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>The Caspian Sea, which meets Azerbaijan at the city of Baku, has no outlet to the ocean, so its level rises and falls with the balance between the water that rivers pour into it and the water that evaporates from its surface. A researcher recorded the level of the sea at Baku at several points over nearly three decades and concluded that its long decline has, if anything, been speeding up. That conclusion is best supported by the observation that ______</p>",
