        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>The seeds of a certain wildflower each carry a small, fatty attachment that ants find irresistible; drawn by it, the ants carry the seeds off and bury them underground. Researchers who studied this partnership proposed that the ants' burying of the seeds benefits the plant chiefly by protecting the seeds from fire, since seeds safely buried beneath the soil survive the grass fires that regularly sweep the region and kill any seeds left lying on the surface.</p>",
