        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "hard",
        passage: "<p>A museum curator argues that a group of undated ceramic bowls, which differ from one another in small details of their painted decoration, were nonetheless all made in one and the same workshop. A colleague is skeptical, taking the differences in decoration as a sign that the bowls came from several different hands. The curator, however, maintains that a scientific analysis of the bowls themselves settles the question in favor of a single workshop.</p>",
