        skill: "Command of Evidence",
        difficulty: "medium",
        passage: "<figure style='margin:0 0 14px'><figcaption style='font-weight:600;text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px'>Two Bakeries' Loaves Sold and Returned Unsold in One Week</figcaption><table style='border-collapse:collapse;margin:0 auto;line-height:1.3'><thead><tr><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Bakery</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Loaves baked</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Loaves sold</th><th style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;background:rgba(127,127,127,0.14);font-weight:600;font-size:13px'>Loaves unsold</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>Riverside</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>1,200</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>1,140</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>60</td></tr><tr><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:left'>Old Mill</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>900</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>720</td><td style='border:1px solid currentColor;padding:5px 9px;font-size:13px;text-align:center'>180</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>The owners of two neighborhood bakeries, Riverside and Old Mill, tracked over the course of one week how many loaves each of them baked, how many they managed to sell, and how many they had left over unsold, hoping in this way to judge how well each bakery was matching its baking to the demand for bread. The owners noted that, compared with Old Mill, Riverside ______</p>",
